<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - OIL COOLER AND FILTER - Oil
        Cooler - Cleaning
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="0">
        <title>Cleaning</title>
        <specpara>
            <caution>
                <para>In the event of a bearing failure, the oil cooler bundle must be replaced because debris from a
                    failed bearing cannot be removed from the cooler bundle.
                </para>
            </caution>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Immerse the oil cooler, front header and filter header in a suitable solvent. Flush and
                drain the cooler to remove any residue.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Dry all components thoroughly with filtered compressed air.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
